      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLARETOWN HANNA (6) comes off an average run last start when fifth at Ballarat over 450m behind Aston Fixer (25.93) in a Maiden. Was in the money prior to that. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Has ability and looks hard to stop. PAW TREACLE (3) finished in the minors last time when third (24.02) at this track making it two minors from two runs. Should be in this for a long way. MANTIS BALE (8) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Paw Vine (23.92) in a Maiden. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Can measure up. LEMNOS LASS (7) warrants respect following a recent placing.",
